# sideral curated flatpak remotes. Read by os/build.sh at image build
# (to register + preinstall the curated set into /var/lib/flatpak) and
# by sideral-flatpak-install.service on every boot (idempotent re-add,
# so deployed systems pick up new remotes added in future image rebases).
# Format:
#   <name>  <url-or-flatpakrepo>
# Lines starting with # and blank lines are ignored.

# Flathub — primary community flatpak distribution. The ONLY remote we
# register: every entry in flatpak-manifest installs from flathub. The
# Fedora flatpak registry was previously also registered but unused, and
# its presence broke the live-ISO build because titanoboa's
# `flatpak install --noninteractive -y <bare-ref>` cannot disambiguate
# refs that exist in multiple remotes (e.g. com.github.tchx84.Flatseal
# is in both flathub and fedora). One remote = no ambiguity.
flathub  https://dl.flathub.org/repo/flathub.flatpakrepo
